p: I should probably help Damian warn the Augur about those assassins.
\b\pn, you're so slow!\nThat took you forever!\nAnyways, I think that's the Rare Stone the mayor was talking about, over there.
\bOver on the far right of the cave, you can't miss it.
\bI assume you have your grunts there, too?
\rYes, and armed with our strongest Pokemon.\nOnce we get rid of the Augur, we'll finally be able to go about our plans uninterrupted!
\bBwa ha ha ha ha...\nExcellent. I'm really not a fan of Jaern.\nThe First Augur, while our enemy, I could at least respect!
\rWell, we won't have to worry about him after today, will we?
\bDid you hear what they were saying?\nThey're after the Augur in Telnor Town!
\bI can't believe we're caught up in the middle of this.
\bWe... we need to help!\nWe need to go back and warn him!\nWho knows what could happen if we don't?
\bWe have to hurry! He might already have arrived!
\b\pn, you're so slow!\nThat took you forever!\nAnyways, I think that's the Rare Stone the mayor was talking about, over there.
\bOver on the far right of the cave, you can't miss it.
???: \bHe will not leave Telnor Town alive.
\bMy agent is already in place.\nI assume yours is, too?
\rYes, and armed to the brink with the strongest of Pokemon.\nRest assured, he will be dead before he leaves Telnor Town.

Very good.
This Augur disgusts me.
I could at least grudgingly respect the first one, but this one is just useless.
He's practically
brainwashed the entire region with all this propaganda he's spread about himself.
\bHave you heard how ridiculous some of it is?\nHe was born of fire and lightning and he rode Xerneas as a steed?\nThe man's been Augur for a year, and
already the people are worshipping him.
\rWell, we won't have to worry about him after today, will we?\nLet's get going.
\bDid you hear what they were saying?\nThey're planning to assassinate the Augur when he comes to Telnor Town!
\bI can't believe we're caught up in the middle of this.
\bWe... we need to help!\nWe need to go back and warn the Augur before the assassins get to him!
\bWe have to hurry! The Augur might already have arrived!
